#Text=Wausau
#Text=Wausau is a city in North Central Wisconsin .
#Text=While the metropolitan area has a population of around 80,000 , it has a big city feel and often leads one to believe they are in a larger city .

#Text=Wausau has many great man-made and natural features , such as Dudley Tower/First Wausau Tower , the tallest commercial building in the state outside of Milwaukee , and Rib Mountain State Park/Granite Peak Ski Area .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Traveling north and south , Wausau can be reached via I-39/US-51 , and traveling east and west , Wausau can be reached by State Highway 29 .
#Text=Wausau can be reached from Minneapolis in about three and a half hours via I-94 and State Highway 29 .
#Text=Milwaukee is about three and a half hours away as well via I-94 and I-39 .

#Text=Central Wisconsin Airport ( CWA ) , 12 miles south of Wausau , provides daily service to and from Detroit ( Delta Air Lines ) , Minneapolis ( Delta Air Lines ) , Chicago O'Hare ( American Airlines or United Airlines ) .
#Text=Lamers Bus Lines offers a daily trip to/from Milwaukee via the Fox Valley which may be ticketed through Greyhound ( or Amtrak if connecting to a rail leg ) .
#Text=Wausau Downtown Airport
#Text=( AUW ) .
#Text=A General aviation airport
#Text=By bus
#Text=Public transportation is limited in the Wausau Area .

#Text=Metro Ride ( formerly WATS or Wausau Area Transit System ) operates eight bus routes in the City of Wausau which run at 30-minute intervals ; one bus route in the Village of Weston , which runs at 30-minute intervals ; and one bus route to Rothschild and Schofield , which operates at 60-minute intervals .
#Text=Passengers can transfer between routes at the Metro Ride Transit Center , which is located at 555 Jefferson Street in the downtown Wausau , one block from the Wausau Center Mall .
#Text=Passengers can also transfer between Route C and Route K at Shopko in Rothschild and between Route E and Route I at Aspirus Clinic in Wausau .
#Text=Buses are clean and uncrowded but the limited schedule makes them somewhat impractical to all but the most dedicated transit user .
#Text=By car
#Text=Travel by car is very easy in the Wausau area and the preferred method of transportation .
#Text=Roads are well maintained and marked .
#Text=Ample , free , at-door parking is available everywhere outside of the downtown area .
#Text=Downtown , parking is easy to find and very inexpensive .

#Text=As the city and surrounding area are oriented north/south , for trips from the far north to far south side or vice versa , it is quicker and easier to use the US 51/I 39 expressway which runs along the west edge of the city .
#Text=See
#Text=Leigh Yawkey Woodson Art Museum
#Text=, 700 North Twelfth Street , ☏ +1715 845-7010 .
#Text=Tuesday - Friday : 9AM-4PM , Saturday - Sunday : Noon - 5PM. .
#Text=The Museum 's permanent collection is known for its focus on nature with historic and contemporary paintings , sculptures , and works on paper that focus on birds .
#Text=The annual Birds in Art exhibition in September and October attracts both international artists and visitors .
#Text=The gardens dotted with sculpture invite visitors to " outdoor galleries .
